i look down the earth, there i step on it

pavan vasu mi vaibum hrang ammacha

Chọdu̠ khuwngto Asān te pachọ du̠ dọnu̠
Long time ago, what we called the salt spring
pachọ du̠to le...lam eso pathung tuwng,
Salt water, far away in an uninhabited place
It was guarded by a tiger
People were afraid of it, so
Amathung tuwng irang....hangthinu mi jọọng tuwng
they woke up early in the morning
chọdu̠ to pachọ to vasu̠ chava
akumikheh te Kau̠ kane ki Saru danu
Some people, fetch water for their relatives
va u̠ vane ki saru supenu
They took a share for their siblings

alal pāl oh, nahla pāl oh
A man's life, a lady's life
It has a great scent, it's a tree
as well as the sick and needy
so the youth's life is compared with
Alal pāl oh nahla pāl oh
both man and women of young age
that is the example of youthful life
because of the fish eaten by the water cat,
a man is drown in the river
when I throw a thing behind the woods
they say you are the only one
but when I reach a mountain
I am considered a dead fool

mituwng nāpapa sosoo nāpapa sosoo nu
eating a sweet potato made the throat itchy
Eating a raw taro didn't make our throat itch
while eating a yam makes it itchy
The person who should be angry,
be troubled, does not feel bad
while the person who wasn't supposed to feel bad does.
He did not know that the person would get angry.

nothing of his business - he got angry about it

i thought of replying my owner but

vama to vatol tol nu hli bāl to vave mang
their works in the field are accomplished quickly

beel ekusa pho phana vāphu va

Pretending/playing the role of a witch..
miing nung vanaṭo to, panal nu

dahdah mo danu pano chọọ chọọ nu
eṭha jahrang to panal chọọ chọọ nu amato
which was to be alright but still greedy after that. That thing means
Pretending/playing the role of a witch..
Throwing/showing a heart of a witch.
Vanaṭo to mi te thimi rende,
Though people dont know the bad things she did,
yet if asked, in their heart
it just comes to their mind
and these bad deed still remain
mi ama kho vāsel ma varende
Even though people were not talking about him
mi kho vāsel thung, vapalung to ahang thuw joo nu
but of other people,and still bang his thoughts
possessing the heart of a witch
Hey, they are talking of me,
inside the water -- from the river bottom

Du̠ralha ngha vana e to aku̠ra thimi

could see the hearts and feeling of other people
Du̠ralki ngha e ithi lulu va vadamang

Danite, da da nung nanaṭo he
It means, in whatever we do
we sometimes regret for the thing we did
Vaduha phadoh sin te lapanu̠ to buma vanida,
but if we put the ladder earlier, the old lady would have not fall
Tuparende vabuh thal tuwng sangla vapha
so putting the ladder after the old lady falls..
we should have put it earlier
Changhal ruwng Jote he, vamasa hin aṭol ka

Une cha va e ida so amka
we believed they are of the same family
If the wild cat dies, the domestic cat mourns
Changhal vathọni jote to vapalung ve pā ka
If the wild cat dies, the domestic cat mourns
Blowing a flute in an elephant's ear
Pashe na vahno lo nate tiise to
When the ear of an elephant moves
nāte Tiise to hi hu hi hu
One blows a flute "hi hu hi hu"
Du̠wm joso pashe na thung Darah kanama cha
but the sound is useless to the elephant's ear
To pour water on a pan leaf.
Andol hna vanadahe najuhle ki enal anāl
The leaf of a pan, when water is poured on it, it slips off
Not a drop of water remains on the leaf
If water is poured on paper,
te du̠ amka, andol hna len be
water remains but on the leaf of a pan
means: even if we keep on giving advices
Ocha pethe so vapalung thung dara ishang ma
mi pethe pe joso pehmal dodoh
He just keeps forgeting the advices
Amato andol hna leen du̠ ihli
which is compared to pouring water on a pan leaf

oh kanu̠ te ahmi vate da che chu̠chu̠ nu
Oh my mother's face is so ugly
Nang so dache chu̠ jānu̠ oh
your face is also the same
iṭol chaja ki mithung tuwng peenu̠ peenu̠ jāvasin

Nahmal nare ṭung joso nadā heengheeng
Our guests are the same as us
Thalna, for example (Eng.), nathungki na inthung ki nachal- nachal- nachalnu̠
For example: our own sister is at home

Even if their dad marries another girl and brings her home,
va u̠, vane hin nung ṭo lulu
she would also do the same works
done by the rest of the family
jowlko in thung jowlko iṭung, same aṭol cha janu
A big butt guest arriving at the big butt's inn is the same..
damo akhe ṭodo joso peenal te...
Even if he does something for someone he still wants it for himself

he gives it with a selfish heart
Which is of no use to others too
Ama palungthu to panu vāngsāng ike ja

tunate chari vathal hate peepeeno ṭeṭe

Amato salhmi- sal jolnu sal hmi len ike

sọpa iṭo he ma lum mo
Does she know how to serve?
da iṭo he ma lummo, ana- nang an- anakah hrang te
does she know how to work? but what you benefit is
one who knows how to work,who is active

so, you will not be fed by beauty

Hlung l- Hlung la ki bahra
Ston- A sweet potato between two stones
One stone here, the other is also here
vāla thung tuwng bahra to hmunu

piihol nare ṭhamanu, hu ha kheh hlung

paru̠wl he amachu te vangchun doso

you shouldn't swear about it and speak of it.
Changhal e ruw pahle jā vati

inung ṭutu, ale ṭuṭu jenu atarāngki
changhal e len athe ale ṭuṭu ale ṭuṭu ale ṭuṭu kaje
on the wild cats dung and play

you are like the wild cats dung and the butterfly means,
amato, unsah elo pa lulu amka vadanava
You love one another so much and stay together.
Pahlu̠ng he ahang phol jojo ahang phol jojo jenu

but the next day we see only the two of them

athe vavang chọ vavang chọ vavang chọ vavang chọ

eṭo eṭo lele eṭo lele jenu

eh eṭo bol jenu, ata eṭo lolo eṭolo jenu

Mi sāram eṭo bol ichọ nibe
If a couple always walks together
they are like the moth couple..we state
Making war basket before the war

He shot the arrows like this
naheka thungte amachu rahe pachule thaning danu

Naheka va amato paṭhal sinnu leleha naheka tol va

kapalungthu ruw kasal ka aṭol manu

most of the people could not achieve it
